    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="9"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d9">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9941</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Aide-Mémoire</hi>
                </p>
                <p>In view of the growing likelihood of an appeal being made to the League of
                    Nations in connexion with the situation in the Far East, His Majesty’s
                    Government in the United Kingdom are anxious to learn whether the United States
                    Government contemplate being represented at Geneva in any way if this event
                    arises. According to the Chinese Ambassador in London the Chinese Government
                    intend to make such an appeal to the League.</p>
                <p>2. His Majesty’s Government are anxious to keep in touch with the United States
                    Government in dealing with the situation, and the French Government have
                    informed them that they share this desire.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-31">August 31,
                            1937</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
